author: Paul Cullen
title: Coronavirus: Italy, Austria and UK account for most imported cases
description: HSE report shows young people, while far less likely to get virus, have been hospitalised
content:
People returning from Italy, Austria and the UK account for most of the travel-related coronavirus cases that have been diagnosed in Ireland to date, an analysis of confirmed infections finds.
